<seg id="107">The Slovak Tax Office requested the delivery of goods (footwear) in the third quarter of 2004 from a Slovak payer totalling SK 2,847 thousand.</seg>
<seg id="108">The Tax Office in the Czech Republic replied that the Czech payer indicated the acquisition of goods of this value only in an additional VAT return and delivered the same goods to Slovak tax entities worth CZK 2,550 by the end of 2004.</seg>
<seg id="109">On the basis of international cooperation between the SAO, the Czech Republic and the SAO SR, it was found that the local tax authority fully recognised the Slovak supplier as entitled to an excessive deduction of VAT incurred, inter alia, on the basis of this supply.</seg>
<seg id="110">This tax office did not provide information about the suspected reexportation to the local tax authorities of the relevant customers of goods imported back from the Czech payer.</seg>
<seg id="111">This will give rise to further examination of commercial activities in connection with possible carousel fraud.</seg>
