<seg id="150">5. International exchange of information between customs authorities of the Czech Republic and Slovakia</seg>
<seg id="151">Until 30 June 2005, the conditions for cooperation between the administrative authorities of the Member States responsible for the management of excise duties were regulated by Council Directive 77/799/EHS on mutual assistance between the competent authorities of the Member States in the field of direct taxes, certain excise duties and insurance premiums.</seg>
<seg id="152">Regulation No 2073/2004, laying down rules and procedures allowing the competent authorities of the Member States of the European Union to cooperate and exchange the information necessary for the correct assessment of excise duties, entered into force on 1 July 2005.</seg>
<seg id="153">Each Member State shall designate a central liaison office to ensure contacts with other Member States in the field of excise duty management and shall be responsible for exchanging information on the movement of excise goods.</seg>
<seg id="154">In the Czech Republic, the report "Excise Liaison Office" (hereinafter referred to as "ELO CR") was set up at the GŘC to ensure the exchange of information in the field of excise taxes between Member States of the European Union.</seg>
<seg id="155">With effect from 1 May 2004, the ELO Office at Poprad carried out security tasks related to the management of systems for controlling the movement of excise goods (SEED, MVS, EWSE) and the exchange of information in the framework of mutual administrative assistance between the Member States of the European Union and the SR.</seg>
