<seg id="157">In accordance with the provisions of Article 3 (1) of the Treaty. 3 Regulation No 2073/2004, the central liaison office shall be responsible, in particular, for - the exchange of data kept in the SEED electronic register, - the Early Warning System Excise (EWSE), - requests for verification of movements of excise goods dispatched to other Member States or received from them by the Movement Verification System (</seg>
<seg id="158">The content, scope and functionality of the SEED, EWSE and MVS systems are modified in Articles 22, 23 and 24 of Regulation No 2073/2004.</seg>
<seg id="159">SEED - a system for the exchange of information on tax entities trading in excise goods.</seg>
