<seg id="161">Each national register shall be made available to the competent authorities of the other Member States only for excise purposes.</seg>
<seg id="162">The central liaison office of each Member State shall ensure that persons involved in the movement of excise goods within the territory of the European Union can obtain confirmation of the information stored in that database.</seg>
<seg id="163">In accordance with Section 41 of Law No 98/2004 Z. z., with Section 39 of Act No. 104/2004 Z. z., with Section 46 of Act No. 105/2004 Z. z., with Section 40 of Act No. 106/2004 Z. z. and with Section 39 of Act No 107/2004 Z. z. ELO SR maintains an electronic database containing a register of tax warehouse operators, authorised beneficiaries and tax warehouses - the SEED database.</seg>
<seg id="164">Customs offices in SR contribute to the SEED database by registering a tax warehouse, tax warehouse operator or authorised recipient in SysNed application software, which is automatically connected to ELO SR.</seg>
