<seg id="498">4.5 Control of large tax entities</seg>
<seg id="499">4.5.1 Control of large tax entities in the Czech Republic</seg>
<seg id="500">General information</seg>
<seg id="501">The VAT audit of large tax entities is governed by the same rules as that of other tax entities.</seg>
<seg id="502">The procedural procedure for controlling VDS is based on Act No. 337/1992 Coll., on the administration of taxes and charges.</seg>
<seg id="503">The Czech Ministry of Finance defined VDS as natural or legal persons established or established for the purpose of doing business and whose net turnover for the tax period indicated in the personal/corporate income tax return amounted to CZK 2 billion or more.</seg>
<seg id="504">The classification of the tax entity as a VDS took place after the filing of the income tax return for the relevant tax period, for the first time in 2003.</seg>
<seg id="505">The tax entity ceased to be referred to as a VDS if, in three consecutive tax periods since the end of the period when it filed the tax return on the basis of which it was classified among the VDS, its net turnover for the tax period fell below that threshold.</seg>
