<seg id="520">4.5.2 Control of large tax entities in Germany</seg>
<seg id="521">General information</seg>
<seg id="522">VAT controls for large companies are governed by the same rules as tax controls in general, i.e. the relevant provisions are enshrined in the following regulations: • the German Fiscal Code (AO), • the Fiscal Administration Act (FVG), • the Tax Control Regulations (BpO).</seg>
<seg id="523">Other methodological documents are also in force.</seg>
<seg id="524">German Fiscal Code</seg>
<seg id="525">The statutory control provisions are enshrined in Articles 193-203 of the German Fiscal Code in Section IV - On-the-Spot Tax Check. In particular, these Articles lay down the rules on the admissibility of on-the-spot tax checks (i.e. at the premises of an undertaking), their scope in terms of subject matter, the rules on the division of responsibilities, the form and content of the control notices, the principles of control, the taxpayer's obligation to cooperate and the prerequisites for carrying out the final discussion and communication of the control report.</seg>
<seg id="526">On-the-spot tax checks are carried out by the responsible tax authorities (Article 195 of the Code).</seg>
<seg id="527">Fiscal Administration Act Pursuant to Article 5.1 (1) in connection with Art. 19 of the Act is compulsory to participate in on-the-spot tax checks carried out by the Financial Authorities for the Federal Central Financial Office.</seg>
<seg id="528">The participating authorities shall agree on the nature and extent of the participation of the Federal Central Tax Office in the tax controls.</seg>
<seg id="529">In addition, the Federal Central Tax Office has the right to require that the specific undertakings it selects are subject to scrutiny at the time it determines.</seg>
<seg id="530">In such a case, it may declare the rules on the conduct and content of inspections at the premises of such companies.</seg>
<seg id="531">Regulations on tax controls According to Article 108.7 of the German Constitution, the provisions on tax checks (German abbreviation BpO 2000) were agreed by the Federal Council (Bundesrat, upper house of the German Parliament, in which the governments of the Länder are represented).</seg>
<seg id="532">These administrative provisions apply to on-the-spot checks by the financial offices of the Länder and the Federal Central Tax Office.</seg>
<seg id="533">Undertakings shall be classified by size at regular intervals in accordance with Article 3 BpO 2000.</seg>
<seg id="534">Large enterprises are subject to follow-up (Article 4.2 BpO).</seg>
<seg id="535">According to Article 33.1 BpO 2000, each informed tax office must keep a register of groups of companies as defined in BpO 2000.</seg>
